label: amenityFeature
definitions: An amenity feature (e.g. a characteristic or service) of the Accommodation. This generic property does not make a statement about whether the feature is included in an offer for the main accommodation or available at extra costs.

label: characterAttribute
definitions: A piece of data that represents a particular aspect of a fictional character (skill, power, character points, advantage, disadvantage).

label: itemCondition
definitions: A predefined value from OfferItemCondition or a textual description of the condition of the product or service, or the products or services included in the offer.

label: accessibilityFeature
definitions: Content features of the resource, such as accessible media, alternatives and supported enhancements for accessibility (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

label: additionalProperty
definitions:
A property-value pair representing an additional characteristics of the entitity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.
Note: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. http://schema.org/width, http://schema.org/color, http://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.

label: benefits
definitions: Description of benefits associated with the job.

label: color-schema
definitions: The color of the product.

label: depth
definitions: The depth of the item.

label: educationRequirements
definitions: Educational background needed for the position or Occupation.

label: experienceRequirements
definitions: Description of skills and experience needed for the position or Occupation.

label: free
definitions: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

label: gender
definitions: Gender of the person. While http://schema.org/Male and http://schema.org/Female may be used, text strings are also acceptable for people who do not identify as a binary gender.

label: height
definitions: The height of the item.

label: incentiveCompensation
definitions: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

label: incentives
definitions: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

label: isLiveBroadcast
definitions: True is the broadcast is of a live event.

label: jobBenefits
definitions: Description of benefits associated with the job.

label: publicAccess
definitions: A flag to signal that the Place is open to public visitors. If this property is omitted there is no assumed default boolean value

label: qualifications
definitions: Specific qualifications required for this role or Occupation.

label: requiredGender
definitions: Audiences defined by a person's gender.

label: responsibilities
definitions: Responsibilities associated with this role or Occupation.

label: skills
definitions: Skills required to fulfill this role or in this Occupation.

label: smokingAllowed
definitions: Indicates whether it is allowed to smoke in the place, e.g. in the restaurant, hotel or hotel room.

label: suggestedGender
definitions: The gender of the person or audience.

label: suitableForDiet
definitions: Indicates a dietary restriction or guideline for which this recipe or menu item is suitable, e.g. diabetic, halal etc.

label: vehicleInteriorColor
definitions: The color or color combination of the interior of the vehicle.

label: videoQuality
definitions: The quality of the video.

label: width
definitions: The width of the item.

label: hasPOS
definitions: Points-of-Sales operated by the organization or person.

label: quest
definitions: The task that a player-controlled character, or group of characters may complete in order to gain a reward.

label: accessibilityHazard
definitions: A characteristic of the described resource that is physiologically dangerous to some users. Related to WCAG 2.0 guideline 2.3 (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

label: httpMethod
definitions: An HTTP method that specifies the appropriate HTTP method for a request to an HTTP EntryPoint. Values are capitalized strings as used in HTTP.

label: mealService
definitions: Description of the meals that will be provided or available for purchase.

label: multipleValues
definitions: Whether multiple values are allowed for the property.  Default is false.

label: readonlyValue
definitions: Whether or not a property is mutable.  Default is false. Specifying this for a property that also has a value makes it act similar to a "hidden" input in an HTML form.

label: valueAddedTaxIncluded
definitions: Specifies whether the applicable value-added tax (VAT) is included in the price specification or not.

label: valueRequired
definitions: Whether the property must be filled in to complete the action.  Default is false.

label: playMode
definitions: Indicates whether this game is multi-player, co-op or single-player.  The game can be marked as multi-player, co-op and single-player at the same time.

label: steeringPosition
definitions: The position of the steering wheel or similar device (mostly for cars).

label: accessMode
definitions: The human sensory perceptual system or cognitive faculty through which a person may process or perceive information. Expected values include: auditory, tactile, textual, visual, colorDependent, chartOnVisual, chemOnVisual, diagramOnVisual, mathOnVisual, musicOnVisual, textOnVisual.

label: accessModeSufficient
definitions: A list of single or combined accessModes that are sufficient to understand all the intellectual content of a resource. Expected values include:  auditory, tactile, textual, visual.

label: artform
definitions: e.g. Painting, Drawing, Sculpture, Print, Photograph, Assemblage, Collage, etc.

label: articleBody
definitions: The actual body of the article.

label: artworkSurface
definitions: The supporting materials for the artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.

label: box
definitions: A box is the area enclosed by the rectangle formed by two points. The first point is the lower corner, the second point is the upper corner. A box is expressed as two points separated by a space character.

label: broadcastServiceTier
definitions: The type of service required to have access to the channel (e.g. Standard or Premium).

label: circle
definitions: A circle is the circular region of a specified radius centered at a specified latitude and longitude. A circle is expressed as a pair followed by a radius in meters.

label: cookingMethod
definitions: The method of cooking, such as Frying, Steaming, ...

label: courseMode
definitions: The medium or means of delivery of the course instance or the mode of study, either as a text label (e.g. "online", "onsite" or "blended"; "synchronous" or "asynchronous"; "full-time" or "part-time") or as a URL reference to a term from a controlled vocabulary (e.g. https://ceds.ed.gov/element/001311#Asynchronous ).

label: driveWheelConfiguration
definitions: The drive wheel configuration, i.e. which roadwheels will receive torque from the vehicle's engine via the drivetrain.

label: encodingFormat
definitions:
Media type typically expressed using a MIME format (see IANA site and MDN reference) e.g. application/zip for a SoftwareApplication binary, audio/mpeg for .mp3 etc.).
In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, encoding can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular encodingFormat information.
Unregistered or niche encoding and file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia/Wikidata entry.

label: fileFormat-schema
definitions: Media type, typically MIME format (see IANA site) of the content e.g. application/zip of a SoftwareApplication binary. In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, 'encoding' can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular fileFormat information. Unregistered or niche file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia entry.

label: line
definitions: A line is a point-to-point path consisting of two or more points. A line is expressed as a series of two or more point objects separated by space.

label: mainContentOfPage
definitions: Indicates if this web page element is the main subject of the page.

label: musicCompositionForm
definitions: The type of composition (e.g. overture, sonata, symphony, etc.).

label: namedPosition
definitions: A position played, performed or filled by a person or organization, as part of an organization. For example, an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.

label: polygon
definitions: A polygon is the area enclosed by a point-to-point path for which the starting and ending points are the same. A polygon is expressed as a series of four or more space delimited points where the first and final points are identical.

label: programmingModel
definitions: Indicates whether API is managed or unmanaged.

label: providerMobility
definitions: Indicates the mobility of a provided service (e.g. 'static', 'dynamic').

label: recipeCuisine
definitions: The cuisine of the recipe (for example, French or Ethiopian).

label: reviewBody
definitions: The actual body of the review.

label: servesCuisine
definitions: The cuisine of the restaurant.

label: surface
definitions: A material used as a surface in some artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.

label: targetPlatform
definitions: Type of app development: phone, Metro style, desktop, XBox, etc.

label: text
definitions: The textual content of this CreativeWork.

label: valuePattern
definitions: Specifies a regular expression for testing literal values according to the HTML spec.

label: vehicleConfiguration
definitions: A short text indicating the configuration of the vehicle, e.g. '5dr hatchback ST 2.5 MT 225 hp' or 'limited edition'.

label: videoFrameSize
definitions: The frame size of the video.

label: calories
definitions: The number of calories.

label: distance
definitions: The distance travelled, e.g. exercising or travelling.

label: additionalNumberOfGuests
definitions: If responding yes, the number of guests who will attend in addition to the invitee.

label: advanceBookingRequirement
definitions: The amount of time that is required between accepting the offer and the actual usage of the resource or service.

label: amount
definitions: The amount of money.

label: amountOfThisGood
definitions: The quantity of the goods included in the offer.

label: annualPercentageRate
definitions: The annual rate that is charged for borrowing (or made by investing), expressed as a single percentage number that represents the actual yearly cost of funds over the term of a loan. This includes any fees or additional costs associated with the transaction.

label: answerCount
definitions: The number of answers this question has received.

label: artEdition
definitions: The number of copies when multiple copies of a piece of artwork are produced - e.g. for a limited edition of 20 prints, 'artEdition' refers to the total number of copies (in this example "20").

label: baseSalary
definitions: The base salary of the job or of an employee in an EmployeeRole.

label: bestRating
definitions: The highest value allowed in this rating system. If bestRating is omitted, 5 is assumed.

label: billingIncrement
definitions: This property specifies the minimal quantity and rounding increment that will be the basis for the billing. The unit of measurement is specified by the unitCode property.

label: bitrate
definitions: The bitrate of the media object.

label: carbohydrateContent
definitions: The number of grams of carbohydrates.

label: cargoVolume
definitions:
The available volume for cargo or luggage. For automobiles, this is usually the trunk volume.
Typical unit code(s): LTR for liters, FTQ for cubic foot/feet
Note: You can use minValue and maxValue to indicate ranges.

label: childMaxAge
definitions: Maximal age of the child.

label: childMinAge
definitions: Minimal age of the child.

label: cholesterolContent
definitions: The number of milligrams of cholesterol.

label: commentCount
definitions: The number of comments this CreativeWork (e.g. Article, Question or Answer) has received. This is most applicable to works published in Web sites with commenting system; additional comments may exist elsewhere.

label: contentSize
definitions: File size in (mega/kilo) bytes.

label: copyrightYear
definitions: The year during which the claimed copyright for the CreativeWork was first asserted.

label: currenciesAccepted
definitions:
The currency accepted.
Use standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

label: currency-schema
definitions:
The currency in which the monetary amount is expressed.
Use standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR"., The currency in which the monetary amount is expressed (in 3-letter ISO 4217 format).

label: defaultValue
definitions: The default value of the input.  For properties that expect a literal, the default is a literal value, for properties that expect an object, it's an ID reference to one of the current values.

label: deliveryLeadTime
definitions: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup.

label: discount
definitions: Any discount applied (to an Order).

label: discountCurrency
definitions:
The currency of the discount.
Use standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

label: downvoteCount
definitions: The number of downvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

label: durationOfWarranty
definitions: The duration of the warranty promise. Common unitCode values are ANN for year, MON for months, or DAY for days.

label: elevation
definitions: The elevation of a location (WGS 84).

label: eligibleDuration
definitions: The duration for which the given offer is valid.

label: eligibleQuantity
definitions: The interval and unit of measurement of ordering quantities for which the offer or price specification is valid. This allows e.g. specifying that a certain freight charge is valid only for a certain quantity.

label: estimatedCost
definitions: The estimated cost of the supply or supplies consumed when performing instructions.

label: fatContent
definitions: The number of grams of fat.

label: fiberContent
definitions: The number of grams of fiber.

label: fileSize
definitions: Size of the application / package (e.g. 18MB). In the absence of a unit (MB, KB etc.), KB will be assumed.

label: flightDistance
definitions: The distance of the flight.

label: floorSize
definitions: The size of the accommodation, e.g. in square meter or squarefoot. Typical unit code(s): MTK for square meter, FTK for square foot, or YDK for square yard

label: fuelConsumption
definitions:
The amount of fuel consumed for traveling a particular distance or temporal duration with the given vehicle (e.g. liters per 100 km).
  • Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for liters per 100 km. Use unitText to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. L/100 km.
  • Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, fuelConsumption (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and fuelEfficiency (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
  • Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use valueReference to link the value for the fuel consumption to another value.

label: fuelEfficiency
definitions:
The distance traveled per unit of fuel used; most commonly miles per gallon (mpg) or kilometers per liter (km/L).
  • Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for miles per gallon or kilometers per liter. Use unitText to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. mpg or km/L.
  • Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, fuelConsumption (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and fuelEfficiency (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
  • Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use valueReference to link the value for the fuel economy to another value.

label: geoMidpoint
definitions: Indicates the GeoCoordinates at the centre of a GeoShape e.g. GeoCircle.

label: geoRadius
definitions: Indicates the approximate radius of a GeoCircle (metres unless indicated otherwise via Distance notation).

label: highPrice
definitions: The highest price of all offers available.

label: interestRate
definitions: The interest rate, charged or paid, applicable to the financial product. Note: This is different from the calculated annualPercentageRate.

label: inventoryLevel
definitions: The current approximate inventory level for the item or items.

label: latitude
definitions: The latitude of a location. For example 37.42242 (WGS 84).

label: loanTerm
definitions: The duration of the loan or credit agreement.

label: longitude
definitions: The longitude of a location. For example -122.08585 (WGS 84).

label: lowPrice
definitions: The lowest price of all offers available.

label: maximumAttendeeCapacity
definitions: The total number of individuals that may attend an event or venue.

label: maxPrice
definitions: The highest price if the price is a range.

label: maxValue
definitions: The upper value of some characteristic or property.

label: memoryRequirements
definitions: Minimum memory requirements.

label: mileageFromOdometer
definitions:
The total distance travelled by the particular vehicle since its initial production, as read from its odometer.
Typical unit code(s): KMT for kilometers, SMI for statute miles

label: minimumPaymentDue
definitions: The minimum payment required at this time.

label: minPrice
definitions: The lowest price if the price is a range.

label: minValue
definitions: The lower value of some characteristic or property.

label: netWorth
definitions: The total financial value of the person as calculated by subtracting assets from liabilities.

label: numAdults
definitions: The number of adults staying in the unit.

label: numberedPosition
definitions: A number associated with a role in an organization, for example, the number on an athlete's jersey.

label: numberOfAirbags
definitions: The number or type of airbags in the vehicle.

label: numberOfAxles
definitions:
The number of axles.
Typical unit code(s): C62

label: numberOfBeds
definitions: The quantity of the given bed type available in the HotelRoom, Suite, House, or Apartment.

label: numberOfDoors
definitions:
The number of doors.
Typical unit code(s): C62

label: numberOfEmployees
definitions: The number of employees in an organization e.g. business.

label: numberOfEpisodes
definitions: The number of episodes in this season or series.

label: numberOfForwardGears
definitions:
The total number of forward gears available for the transmission system of the vehicle.
Typical unit code(s): C62

label: numberOfItems
definitions: The number of items in an ItemList. Note that some descriptions might not fully describe all items in a list (e.g., multi-page pagination); in such cases, the numberOfItems would be for the entire list.

label: numberOfPages
definitions: The number of pages in the book.

label: numberOfPlayers
definitions: Indicate how many people can play this game (minimum, maximum, or range).

label: numberOfPreviousOwners
definitions:
The number of owners of the vehicle, including the current one.
Typical unit code(s): C62

label: numberOfRooms
definitions: The number of rooms (excluding bathrooms and closets) of the accommodation or lodging business. Typical unit code(s): ROM for room or C62 for no unit. The type of room can be put in the unitText property of the QuantitativeValue.

label: numberOfSeasons
definitions: The number of seasons in this series.

label: numChildren
definitions: The number of children staying in the unit.

label: numTracks
definitions: The number of tracks in this album or playlist.

label: nutrition
definitions: Nutrition information about the recipe or menu item.

label: occupancy
definitions: The allowed total occupancy for the accommodation in persons (including infants etc). For individual accommodations, this is not necessarily the legal maximum but defines the permitted usage as per the contractual agreement (e.g. a double room used by a single person). Typical unit code(s): C62 for person

label: offerCount
definitions: The number of offers for the product.

label: orderQuantity
definitions: The number of the item ordered. If the property is not set, assume the quantity is one.

label: partySize
definitions: Number of people the reservation should accommodate.

label: playersOnline
definitions: Number of players on the server.

label: price
definitions:
The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.
Usage guidelines:
  • Use the priceCurrency property (with standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR") instead of including ambiguous symbols such as '$' in the value.
  • Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.
  • Note that both RDFa and Microdata syntax allow the use of a "content=" attribute for publishing simple machine-readable values alongside more human-friendly formatting.
  • Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.

label: priceComponent
definitions: This property links to all UnitPriceSpecification nodes that apply in parallel for the CompoundPriceSpecification node.

label: priceCurrency
definitions:
The currency of the price, or a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.
Use standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

label: priceRange
definitions: The price range of the business, for example $$$.

label: priceSpecification
definitions: One or more detailed price specifications, indicating the unit price and delivery or payment charges.

label: proteinContent
definitions: The number of grams of protein.

label: ratingCount
definitions: The count of total number of ratings.

label: ratingValue
definitions: The rating for the content.

label: recipeYield
definitions: The quantity produced by the recipe (for example, number of people served, number of servings, etc).

label: referenceQuantity
definitions: The reference quantity for which a certain price applies, e.g. 1 EUR per 4 kWh of electricity. This property is a replacement for unitOfMeasurement for the advanced cases where the price does not relate to a standard unit.

label: remainingAttendeeCapacity
definitions: The number of attendee places for an event that remain unallocated.

label: requiredCollateral
definitions: Assets required to secure loan or credit repayments. It may take form of third party pledge, goods, financial instruments (cash, securities, etc.)

label: requiredMaxAge
definitions: Audiences defined by a person's maximum age.

label: requiredMinAge
definitions: Audiences defined by a person's minimum age.

label: requiredQuantity
definitions: The required quantity of the item(s).

label: reviewCount
definitions: The count of total number of reviews.

label: salaryCurrency
definitions: The currency (coded using ISO 4217 ) used for the main salary information in this job posting or for this employee.

label: saturatedFatContent
definitions: The number of grams of saturated fat.

label: screenCount
definitions: The number of screens in the movie theater.

label: servingSize
definitions: The serving size, in terms of the number of volume or mass.

label: sodiumContent
definitions: The number of milligrams of sodium.

label: stepValue
definitions: The stepValue attribute indicates the granularity that is expected (and required) of the value in a PropertyValueSpecification.

label: sugarContent
definitions: The number of grams of sugar.

label: suggestedMaxAge
definitions: Maximal age recommended for viewing content.

label: suggestedMinAge
definitions: Minimal age recommended for viewing content.

label: totalPaymentDue
definitions: The total amount due.

label: totalPrice
definitions: The total price for the reservation or ticket, including applicable taxes, shipping, etc.

label: transFatContent
definitions: The number of grams of trans fat.

label: typicalAgeRange
definitions: The typical expected age range, e.g. '7-9', '11-'.

label: unitText
definitions: A string or text indicating the unit of measurement. Useful if you cannot provide a standard unit code for unitCode.

label: unsaturatedFatContent
definitions: The number of grams of unsaturated fat.

label: upvoteCount
definitions: The number of upvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

label: userInteractionCount
definitions: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication.

label: value
definitions:
The value of the quantitative value or property value node.
  • For QuantitativeValue and MonetaryAmount, the recommended type for values is 'Number'.
  • For PropertyValue, it can be 'Text;', 'Number', 'Boolean', or 'StructuredValue'.

label: valueMaxLength
definitions: Specifies the allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

label: valueMinLength
definitions: Specifies the minimum allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

label: vehicleSeatingCapacity
definitions:
The number of passengers that can be seated in the vehicle, both in terms of the physical space available, and in terms of limitations set by law.
Typical unit code(s): C62 for persons.

label: version
definitions: The version of the CreativeWork embodied by a specified resource.

label: weight
definitions: The weight of the product or person.

label: wordCount
definitions: The number of words in the text of the Article.

label: worstRating
definitions: The lowest value allowed in this rating system. If worstRating is omitted, 1 is assumed.

label: yearlyRevenue
definitions: The size of the business in annual revenue.

label: yearsInOperation
definitions: The age of the business.

label: yield
definitions: The quantity that results by performing instructions. For example, a paper airplane, 10 personalized candles.

label: broadcastOfEvent
definitions: The event being broadcast such as a sporting event or awards ceremony.

label: containsSeason
definitions: A season that is part of the media series.

label: dayOfWeek
definitions: The day of the week for which these opening hours are valid.

label: event
definitions: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.
domainIncludes: http://schema.org/InformAction, http://schema.org/InviteAction, http://schema.org/JoinAction, http://schema.org/LeaveAction, http://schema.org/Organization, http://schema.org/Place, http://schema.org/PlayAction

label: events
definitions: Upcoming or past events associated with this place or organization.

label: firstPerformance
definitions: The date and place the work was first performed.

label: hasCourseInstance
definitions: An offering of the course at a specific time and place or through specific media or mode of study or to a specific section of students.

label: hoursAvailable
definitions: The hours during which this service or contact is available.

label: liveBlogUpdate
definitions: An update to the LiveBlog.

label: openingHoursSpecification
definitions: The opening hours of a certain place.

label: publication
definitions: A publication event associated with the item.

label: publishedOn
definitions: A broadcast service associated with the publication event.

label: recordedIn
definitions: The CreativeWork that captured all or part of this Event.

label: season
definitions: A season in a media series.

label: seasons
definitions: A season in a media series.

label: specialOpeningHoursSpecification
definitions:
The special opening hours of a certain place.
Use this to explicitly override general opening hours brought in scope by openingHoursSpecification or openingHours.

label: subEvent
definitions: An Event that is part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each of which is a subEvent of the conference.

label: subEvents
definitions: Events that are a part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each subEvents of the conference.

label: superEvent
definitions: An event that this event is a part of. For example, a collection of individual music performances might each have a music festival as their superEvent.

label: workFeatured
definitions: A work featured in some event, e.g. exhibited in an ExhibitionEvent. Specific subproperties are available for workPerformed (e.g. a play), or a workPresented (a Movie at a ScreeningEvent).

label: workPerformed
definitions: A work performed in some event, for example a play performed in a TheaterEvent.

label: arrivalTime
definitions: The expected arrival time.

label: availabilityEnds
definitions: The end of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

label: availabilityStarts
definitions: The beginning of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

label: availableFrom
definitions: When the item is available for pickup from the store, locker, etc.

label: availableThrough
definitions: After this date, the item will no longer be available for pickup.

label: billingPeriod
definitions: The time interval used to compute the invoice.

label: birthDate
definitions: Date of birth.

label: bookingTime
definitions: The date and time the reservation was booked.

label: checkinTime
definitions: The earliest someone may check into a lodging establishment.

label: checkoutTime
definitions: The latest someone may check out of a lodging establishment.

label: closes
definitions: The closing hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

label: commentTime
definitions: The time at which the UserComment was made.

label: cookTime
definitions: The time it takes to actually cook the dish, in ISO 8601 duration format.

label: coverageEndTime
definitions: The time when the live blog will stop covering the Event. Note that coverage may continue after the Event concludes.

label: coverageStartTime
definitions: The time when the live blog will begin covering the Event. Note that coverage may begin before the Event's start time. The LiveBlogPosting may also be created before coverage begins.

label: datasetTimeInterval
definitions: The range of temporal applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 (in ISO 8601 time interval format).

label: dateCreated
definitions: The date on which the CreativeWork was created or the item was added to a DataFeed.

label: dateDeleted
definitions: The datetime the item was removed from the DataFeed.

label: dateIssued
definitions: The date the ticket was issued.

label: dateModified
definitions: The date on which the CreativeWork was most recently modified or when the item's entry was modified within a DataFeed.

label: datePosted
definitions: Publication date for the job posting.

label: datePublished
definitions: Date of first broadcast/publication.

label: dateRead
definitions: The date/time at which the message has been read by the recipient if a single recipient exists.

label: dateReceived
definitions: The date/time the message was received if a single recipient exists.

label: dateSent
definitions: The date/time at which the message was sent.

label: dateVehicleFirstRegistered

The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from January to December.

label: expires
definitions: Date the content expires and is no longer useful or available. For example a VideoObject or NewsArticle whose availability or relevance is time-limited, or a ClaimReview fact check whose publisher wants to indicate that it may no longer be relevant (or helpful to highlight) after some date.

label: foundingDate
definitions: The date that this organization was founded.

label: lastReviewed

label: modifiedTime

label: openingHours
definitions:
The general opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'.
  • Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: Mo, Tu, We, Th, Fr, Sa, Su.
  • Times are specified using 24:00 time. For example, 3pm is specified as 15:00.
  • Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>.
  • If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.

label: opens
definitions: The opening hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

label: orderDate
definitions: Date order was placed.

label: ownedFrom

label: ownedThrough
definitions: The date and time of giving up ownership on the product.

label: paymentDue

label: prepTime

label: previousStartDate
definitions: Used in conjunction with eventStatus for rescheduled or cancelled events. This property contains the previously scheduled start date. For rescheduled events, the startDate property should be used for the newly scheduled start date. In the (rare) case of an event that has been postponed and rescheduled multiple times, this field may be repeated.

label: priceValidUntil

label: processingTime

label: productionDate

label: purchaseDate
definitions: The date the item e.g. vehicle was purchased by the current owner.

label: releaseDate
definitions: The release date of a product or product model. This can be used to distinguish the exact variant of a product.

label: scheduledPaymentDate
definitions: The date the invoice is scheduled to be paid.

label: scheduledTime
definitions: The time the object is scheduled to.

label: startDate
definitions: The start date and time of the item (in ISO 8601 date format).

label: startTime
definitions:
The startTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to start. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from January to December.
Note that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

label: temporal
definitions: The range of temporal applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 (in ISO 8601 time interval format).

label: temporalCoverage
definitions: The temporalCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the period that the content applies to, i.e. that it describes, either as a DateTime or as a textual string indicating a time period in ISO 8601 time interval format. In the case of a Dataset it will typically indicate the relevant time period in a precise notation (e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 would be written "2011/2012"). Other forms of content e.g. ScholarlyArticle, Book, TVSeries or TVEpisode may indicate their temporalCoverage in broader terms - textually or via well-known URL. Written works such as books may sometimes have precise temporal coverage too, e.g. a work set in 1939 - 1945 can be indicated in ISO 8601 interval format format via "1939/1945".

label: timeRequired
definitions: Approximate or typical time it takes to work with or through this learning resource for the typical intended target audience, e.g. 'P30M', 'P1H25M'.

label: totalTime
definitions: The total time required to perform instructions or a direction (including time to prepare the supplies), in ISO 8601 duration format.

label: uploadDate
definitions: Date when this media object was uploaded to this site.

label: validFor
definitions: The time validity of the permit.

label: validFrom
definitions: The date when the item becomes valid.

label: validThrough

label: validUntil
definitions: The date when the item is no longer valid.

label: vehicleModelDate
definitions: The release date of a vehicle model (often used to differentiate versions of the same make and model).

label: webCheckinTime
definitions: The time when a passenger can check into the flight online.

label: workHours
definitions: The typical working hours for this job (e.g. 1st shift, night shift, 8am-5pm).

label: acceptedPaymentMethod

label: appliesToPaymentMethod

label: availability

label: bed
definitions: The type of bed or beds included in the accommodation. For the single case of just one bed of a certain type, you use bed directly with a text. If you want to indicate the quantity of a certain kind of bed, use an instance of BedDetails. For more detailed information, use the amenityFeature property.

label: ccRecipient
definitions: A sub property of recipient. The recipient copied on a message.

label: countryOfOrigin

label: deliveryMethod

label: deliveryStatus

label: distribution

label: expectsAcceptanceOf

label: orderDelivery

label: resultReview

label: serviceAudience

label: supportingData

label: targetProduct
definitions: Target Operating System / Product to which the code applies.  If applies to several versions, just the product name can be used.

subproperties: http://schema.org/course, http://schema.org/entertainmentBusiness, http://schema.org/exerciseCourse, http://schema.org/foodEstablishment, http://schema.org/foodEvent, http://schema.org/fromLocation, http://schema.org/homeLocation, http://schema.org/sportsActivityLocation, http://schema.org/sportsEvent, http://schema.org/toLocation, http://schema.org/workLocation

label: dateline
definitions:
A dateline is a brief piece of text included in news articles that describes where and when the story was written or filed though the date is often omitted. Sometimes only a placename is provided.
Structured representations of dateline-related information can also be expressed more explicitly using locationCreated (which represents where a work was created e.g. where a news report was written). For location depicted or described in the content, use contentLocation.
Dateline summaries are oriented more towards human readers than towards automated processing, and can vary substantially. Some examples: "BEIRUT, Lebanon, June 2.", "Paris, France", "December 19, 2017 11:43AM Reporting from Washington", "Beijing/Moscow", "QUEZON CITY, Philippines".

label: departureGate
definitions: Identifier of the flight's departure gate.

label: departurePlatform
definitions: The platform from which the train departs.

label: departureTerminal
definitions: Identifier of the flight's departure terminal.

The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is not valid, e.g. a region where the transaction is not allowed.
See also eligibleRegion.

label: propertyID
definitions: A commonly used identifier for the characteristic represented by the property, e.g. a manufacturer or a standard code for a property. propertyID can be (1) a prefixed string, mainly meant to be used with standards for product properties; (2) a site-specific, non-prefixed string (e.g. the primary key of the property or the vendor-specific id of the property), or (3) a URL indicating the type of the property, either pointing to an external vocabulary, or a Web resource that describes the property (e.g. a glossary entry). Standards bodies should promote a standard prefix for the identifiers of properties from their standards.

definitions: The exchange traded instrument associated with a Corporation object. The tickerSymbol is expressed as an exchange and an instrument name separated by a space character. For the exchange component of the tickerSymbol attribute, we recommend using the controlled vocabulary of Market Identifier Codes (MIC) specified in ISO15022.

label: branchCode
definitions:
A short textual code (also called "store code") that uniquely identifies a place of business. The code is typically assigned by the parentOrganization and used in structured URLs.
For example, in the URL http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047 the code "3047" is a branchCode for a particular branch.

label: cheatCode

label: discountCode

label: gtin13
definitions: The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceeding zero. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

label: gtin14
definitions: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

label: gtin8
definitions: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

label: itemListElement
definitions:
For itemListElement values, you can use simple strings (e.g. "Peter", "Paul", "Mary"), existing entities, or use ListItem.
Text values are best if the elements in the list are plain strings. Existing entities are best for a simple, unordered list of existing things in your data. ListItem is used with ordered lists when you want to provide additional context about the element in that list or when the same item might be in different places in different lists.
Note: The order of elements in your mark-up is not sufficient for indicating the order or elements. Use ListItem with a 'position' property in such cases.

label: itemListOrder
definitions: Type of ordering (e.g. Ascending, Descending, Unordered).

label: nextItem
definitions: A link to the ListItem that follows the current one.

label: position
definitions: The position of an item in a series or sequence of items.

label: previousItem
definitions: A link to the ListItem that preceeds the current one.

label: step
definitions: A single step item (as HowToStep, text, document, video, etc.) or a HowToSection.

label: steps
definitions: A single step item (as HowToStep, text, document, video, etc.) or a HowToSection (originally misnamed 'steps'; 'step' is preferred).

label: publishingPrinciples
definitions:
The publishingPrinciples property indicates (typically via URL) a document describing the editorial principles of an Organization (or individual e.g. a Person writing a blog) that relate to their activities as a publisher, e.g. ethics or diversity policies. When applied to a CreativeWork (e.g. NewsArticle) the principles are those of the party primarily responsible for the creation of the CreativeWork.
While such policies are most typically expressed in natural language, sometimes related information (e.g. indicating a funder) can be expressed using schema.org terminology.

definitions: A sub property of location. The specific food event where the action occurred.

label: founder
definitions: A person who founded this organization.

label: founders
definitions: A person who founded this organization.

label: funder
definitions: A person or organization that supports (sponsors) something through some kind of financial contribution.

label: homeTeam
definitions: The home team in a sports event.

label: illustrator
definitions: The illustrator of the book.

label: instructor
definitions: A person assigned to instruct or provide instructional assistance for the CourseInstance.

label: instrument
definitions: The object that helped the agent perform the action. e.g. John wrote a book with a pen.
subproperties: http://schema.org/deliveryMethod, http://schema.org/diet, http://schema.org/exercisePlan, http://schema.org/exerciseRelatedDiet, http://schema.org/language, http://schema.org/query, http://schema.org/recipe, http://schema.org/supply, http://schema.org/tool

label: interactionType
definitions: The Action representing the type of interaction. For up votes, +1s, etc. use LikeAction. For down votes use DislikeAction. Otherwise, use the most specific Action.

label: landlord
definitions: A sub property of participant. The owner of the real estate property.

label: lender
definitions: A sub property of participant. The person that lends the object being borrowed.

label: loser
definitions: A sub property of participant. The loser of the action.

label: lyricist
definitions: The person who wrote the words.

label: mapType
definitions: Indicates the kind of Map, from the MapCategoryType Enumeration.

label: material
definitions: A material that something is made from, e.g. leather, wool, cotton, paper.

label: member
definitions: A member of an Organization or a ProgramMembership. Organizations can be members of organizations; ProgramMembership is typically for individuals.

label: members
definitions: A member of this organization.

label: merchant
definitions: 'merchant' is an out-dated term for 'seller'.

label: musicGroupMember
definitions: A member of a music group—for example, John, Paul, George, or Ringo.

label: musicReleaseFormat
definitions: Format of this release (the type of recording media used, ie. compact disc, digital media, LP, etc.).

label: opponent
definitions: A sub property of participant. The opponent on this action.

label: organizer
definitions: An organizer of an Event.

label: owns
definitions: Products owned by the organization or person.

label: parent
definitions: A parent of this person.

label: parents
definitions: A parents of the person.

label: parentService
definitions: A broadcast service to which the broadcast service may belong to such as regional variations of a national channel.

label: participant
definitions: Other co-agents that participated in the action indirectly. e.g. John wrote a book with Steve.
subproperties: http://schema.org/borrower, http://schema.org/buyer, http://schema.org/endorsee, http://schema.org/landlord, http://schema.org/lender, http://schema.org/loser, http://schema.org/opponent, http://schema.org/realEstateAgent, http://schema.org/recipient, http://schema.org/seller, http://schema.org/sender, http://schema.org/sportsTeam, http://schema.org/vendor, http://schema.org/winner

label: performer
definitions: A performer at the event—for example, a presenter, musician, musical group or actor.

label: performers
definitions: The main performer or performers of the event—for example, a presenter, musician, or actor.

label: permissionType
definitions: The type of permission granted the person, organization, or audience.

label: producer
definitions: The person or organization who produced the work (e.g. music album, movie, tv/radio series etc.).

label: produces
definitions: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

label: provider
definitions: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.
domainIncludes: http://schema.org/CreativeWork, http://schema.org/Invoice, http://schema.org/ParcelDelivery, http://schema.org/Reservation, http://schema.org/Service, http://schema.org/Trip

label: publisher
definitions: The publisher of the creative work.

label: realEstateAgent
definitions: A sub property of participant. The real estate agent involved in the action.

label: recipe
definitions: A sub property of instrument. The recipe/instructions used to perform the action.

label: relatedTo
definitions: The most generic familial relation.

label: releaseOf
definitions: The album this is a release of.

label: seller
definitions: An entity which offers (sells / leases / lends / loans) the services / goods.  A seller may also be a provider.

label: sibling
definitions: A sibling of the person.

label: siblings
definitions: A sibling of the person.

label: specialty
definitions: One of the domain specialities to which this web page's content applies.

label: sponsor
definitions: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. e.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

label: sportsEvent
definitions: A sub property of location. The sports event where this action occurred.

label: sportsTeam
definitions: A sub property of participant. The sports team that participated on this action.

label: spouse
definitions: The person's spouse.

label: supply
definitions: A sub-property of instrument. A supply consumed when performing instructions or a direction.

label: tool
definitions: A sub property of instrument. An object used (but not consumed) when performing instructions or a direction.

label: touristType
definitions: Attraction suitable for type(s) of tourist. eg. Children, visitors from a particular country, etc.

label: translator
definitions: Organization or person who adapts a creative work to different languages, regional differences and technical requirements of a target market, or that translates during some event.

label: typeOfBed
definitions: The type of bed to which the BedDetail refers, i.e. the type of bed available in the quantity indicated by quantity.

label: typeOfGood
definitions: The product that this structured value is referring to.

label: vendor
definitions: 'vendor' is an earlier term for 'seller'.

label: winner
definitions: A sub property of participant. The winner of the action.

label: additionalType
definitions: An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. In RDFa syntax, it is better to use the native RDFa syntax - the 'typeof' attribute - for multiple types. Schema.org tools may have only weaker understanding of extra types, in particular those defined externally.

label: applicationCategory
definitions: Type of software application, e.g. 'Game, Multimedia'.

label: applicationSubCategory
definitions: Subcategory of the application, e.g. 'Arcade Game'.

label: artMedium
definitions: The material used. (e.g. Oil, Watercolour, Acrylic, Linoprint, Marble, Cyanotype, Digital, Lithograph, DryPoint, Intaglio, Pastel, Woodcut, Pencil, Mixed Media, etc.)

label: assembly
definitions: Library file name e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

label: audienceType
definitions: The target group associated with a given audience (e.g. veterans, car owners, musicians, etc.).

label: award
definitions: An award won by or for this item.

label: awards
definitions: Awards won by or for this item.

label: colleague
definitions: A colleague of the person.

label: contactType
definitions: A person or organization can have different contact points, for different purposes. For example, a sales contact point, a PR contact point and so on. This property is used to specify the kind of contact point.

label: contentType
definitions: The supported content type(s) for an EntryPoint response.

label: device
definitions: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

label: industry-schema
definitions: The industry associated with the job position.

label: interactivityType
definitions: The predominant mode of learning supported by the learning resource. Acceptable values are 'active', 'expositive', or 'mixed'.

label: learningResourceType
definitions: The predominant type or kind characterizing the learning resource. For example, 'presentation', 'handout'.

label: parentItem
definitions: The parent of a question, answer or item in general.

label: sport-schema
definitions: A type of sport (e.g. Baseball).

label: makesOffer
definitions: A pointer to products or services offered by the organization or person.

label: offers
definitions: An offer to provide this item; for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event.
domainIncludes: http://schema.org/AggregateOffer, http://schema.org/CreativeWork, http://schema.org/Event, http://schema.org/MenuItem, http://schema.org/Product, http://schema.org/Service, http://schema.org/Trip

label: potentialAction

label: actionOption
definitions: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

label: option
definitions: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

label: query
definitions: A sub property of instrument. The query used on this action.

label: question
definitions: A sub property of object. A question.

label: accountablePerson
definitions: Specifies the Person that is legally accountable for the CreativeWork.

label: acquiredFrom
definitions: The organization or person from which the product was acquired.

label: affiliation

label: alumniOf
definitions: An organization that the person is an alumni of.

label: appliesToDeliveryMethod
definitions: The delivery method(s) to which the delivery charge or payment charge specification applies.

label: bookingAgent
definitions: 'bookingAgent' is an out-dated term indicating a 'broker' that serves as a booking agent.

label: branchOf
definitions: The larger organization that this local business is a branch of, if any. Not to be confused with (anatomical)branch.

label: broadcastAffiliateOf
definitions: The media network(s) whose content is broadcast on this station.

label: byArtist
definitions: The artist that performed this album or recording.

label: collection-schema
definitions: A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.

label: creditedTo
definitions: The group the release is credited to if different than the byArtist. For example, Red and Blue is credited to "Stefani Germanotta Band", but by Lady Gaga.

label: department
definitions: A relationship between an organization and a department of that organization, also described as an organization (allowing different urls, logos, opening hours). For example: a store with a pharmacy, or a bakery with a cafe.

label: educationalAlignment
definitions: An alignment to an established educational framework.

label: gameServer
definitions: The server on which  it is possible to play the game.

label: grantee
definitions: The person, organization, contact point, or audience that has been granted this permission.

label: hiringOrganization
definitions: Organization offering the job position.

label: hostingOrganization
definitions: The organization (airline, travelers' club, etc.) the membership is made with.

label: inBroadcastLineup
definitions: The CableOrSatelliteService offering the channel.

label: includedComposition
definitions: Smaller compositions included in this work (e.g. a movement in a symphony).

label: includesObject
definitions: This links to a node or nodes indicating the exact quantity of the products included in the offer.

label: inPlaylist
definitions: The playlist to which this recording belongs.

label: isRelatedTo
definitions: A pointer to another, somehow related product (or multiple products).

label: issuedBy
definitions: The organization issuing the ticket or permit.

label: isVariantOf
definitions: A pointer to a base product from which this product is a variant. It is safe to infer that the variant inherits all product features from the base model, unless defined locally. This is not transitive.

label: itemOffered
definitions: The item being offered.

label: itemReviewed
definitions: The item that is being reviewed/rated.

label: itemShipped
definitions: Item(s) being shipped.

label: knows
definitions: The most generic bi-directional social/work relation.

label: manufacturer
definitions: The manufacturer of the product.

label: memberOf

label: musicBy

label: object
definitions: The object upon which the action is carried out, whose state is kept intact or changed. Also known as the semantic roles patient, affected or undergoer (which change their state) or theme (which doesn't). e.g. John read a book.

label: offeredBy

definitions: The thing -- flight, event, restaurant,etc. being reserved.

definitions: The result produced in the action. e.g. John wrote a book.

label: seeks
definitions: A pointer to products or services sought by the organization or person (demand).

definitions: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the sending end of the action.

label: serviceOperator

label: serviceOutput
definitions: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

label: sourceOrganization
definitions: The Organization on whose behalf the creator was working.

label: targetCollection
definitions: A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.

label: toRecipient

label: worksFor
definitions: Organizations that the person works for.

label: availableLanguage
definitions: A language someone may use with or at the item, service or place. Please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard. See also inLanguage

definitions: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

definitions: Requirements for taking the Course. May be completion of another Course or a textual description like "permission of instructor". Requirements may be a pre-requisite competency, referenced using AlignmentObject.

label: educationalRole
definitions: An educationalRole of an EducationalAudience.

label: educationalUse
definitions: The purpose of a work in the context of education; for example, 'assignment', 'group work'.

label: inLanguage
definitions: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard. See also availableLanguage.

label: isAccessibleForFree
definitions: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

label: isFamilyFriendly
definitions: Indicates whether this content is family friendly.

label: isGift
definitions: Was the offer accepted as a gift for someone other than the buyer.

label: language-schema
definitions: A sub property of instrument. The language used on this action.

label: productSupported
definitions: The product or service this support contact point is related to (such as product support for a particular product line). This can be a specific product or product line (e.g. "iPhone") or a general category of products or services (e.g. "smartphones").

label: programmingLanguage-schema
definitions: The computer programming language.

label: subtitleLanguage
definitions: Languages in which subtitles/captions are available, in IETF BCP 47 standard format.

label: musicArrangement
definitions: An arrangement derived from the composition.

label: workPresented
definitions: The movie presented during this event.
